1
00:00:28,541 --> 00:00:30,541
[music playing]

2
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:34,500
[camera shutter clicks]

3
00:01:57,416 --> 00:01:58,375
[producer sighs]

4
00:01:59,333 --> 00:02:00,166
[chuckles]

5
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:02,583
I have a name for our movie.

6
00:02:06,375 --> 00:02:07,666
What name, boss?

7
00:02:08,625 --> 00:02:10,583
Mae Nak Liver's Apes.

8
00:02:10,666 --> 00:02:11,500
[Kheng] Huh?

9
00:02:12,291 --> 00:02:15,625
So you want to remake Mae Nak?

10
00:02:15,708 --> 00:02:17,041
Of course!

11
00:02:17,666 --> 00:02:20,458
Mae Nak...
What does that have to do with apes?

12
00:02:21,958 --> 00:02:26,125
Sheesh! I said, "Mae Nak Liver's Apes."

13
00:02:26,208 --> 00:02:30,333
Nothing to do with apes, you idiot!

14
00:02:30,416 --> 00:02:33,416
Can't you understand Thai?

15
00:02:33,708 --> 00:02:34,583
Oh.

16
00:02:34,666 --> 00:02:36,166
"Mae Nak Riverscape."

17
00:02:36,250 --> 00:02:37,958
-Right.
-[Kheng] Okay.

18
00:02:38,333 --> 00:02:40,458
So what does it have to do with the river?

19
00:02:40,541 --> 00:02:44,083
Well, why does it always have to be
Mae Nak Phra Khanong?

20
00:02:44,291 --> 00:02:46,333
Don't you find it boring?

21
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:51,208
Why can't we come up with
a new idea for Thai movies?

22
00:02:52,458 --> 00:02:54,708
So Mae Nak Riverscape then?

23
00:02:54,791 --> 00:02:57,500
That's right. Mae Nak Liver's Ape.

24
00:02:57,625 --> 00:03:03,000
I'm going to make a new history
for Thai horror.

25
00:03:03,208 --> 00:03:05,166
-Make history?
-Yeah.

26
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:06,750
How?

27
00:03:07,708 --> 00:03:10,875
How the hell would I know?
I'm not a director.

28
00:03:11,041 --> 00:03:13,958
I'm the boss, you idiot!

29
00:03:14,041 --> 00:03:16,125
How is it going to change history?

30
00:03:16,208 --> 00:03:18,625
Ask that asshole over there.
He's the director!

31
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:22,750
Hey, it's all on you, Tukkae.

32
00:03:22,833 --> 00:03:25,416
Mae Nak Riverscape. Got it.

33
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:29,916
So do we have to film

34
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,708
by the actual river?

35
00:03:32,791 --> 00:03:35,125
Are you retarded?

36
00:03:35,208 --> 00:03:37,291
What's the damn title?

37
00:03:37,541 --> 00:03:40,541
Of course, Mae Nak Riverscape

38
00:03:40,625 --> 00:03:42,916
has to be filmed at the Mekong River.

39
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:47,500
It's not Mae Nak Chao Phraya, is it?

40
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:50,000
You big dummy!

41
00:03:50,083 --> 00:03:51,125
[Kheng] Got it. Yes, sir.

42
00:04:05,375 --> 00:04:07,375
[typing]

43
00:04:11,875 --> 00:04:13,875
"NO TITLE"

44
00:04:13,958 --> 00:04:19,000
WRITTEN BY MANA JITMANKONG

45
00:04:19,750 --> 00:04:25,208
EXT. CHIANG KHAN - DAY

46
00:04:45,791 --> 00:04:47,041
What's your name, boy?

47
00:04:47,875 --> 00:04:49,333
My name is Tukkae, sir.

48
00:04:49,666 --> 00:04:50,791
Tukkae? [laughs]

49
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:54,333
What the hell kind of name is that?

50
00:04:58,791 --> 00:05:00,708
So you like painting?

51
00:05:02,625 --> 00:05:04,708
-Yes, sir.
-You want to help me paint?

52
00:05:07,041 --> 00:05:08,041
Yes, sir.

53
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:11,750
You can start by cleaning all my brushes.

54
00:05:12,333 --> 00:05:13,333
Okay, sir.

55
00:05:13,541 --> 00:05:17,708
Here, use this water can.

56
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:24,041
Master Pong, when is this movie
going to premiere?

57
00:05:24,333 --> 00:05:25,958
Soon, Miss Pang.

58
00:05:26,041 --> 00:05:28,375
That's right. Soon.

59
00:05:32,250 --> 00:05:35,000
HANUMAN VS. 7 ULTRAMAN

60
00:05:35,083 --> 00:05:36,583
Hello, Master Pong.

61
00:05:36,666 --> 00:05:38,125
Hello, hello.

62
00:05:38,208 --> 00:05:40,250
Hi, Mother.

63
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:41,333
[Tukkae] Hello, ma'am.

64
00:05:41,416 --> 00:05:42,875
Let's go, Tukkae.

65
00:05:42,958 --> 00:05:45,041
[Tukkae] But I'm not done yet.

66
00:05:45,958 --> 00:05:48,083
Go on.

67
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:50,166
I'll finish it myself.

68
00:05:53,583 --> 00:05:57,291
You like painting, but what do you want
to do when you get older, Tukkae?

69
00:05:57,375 --> 00:06:00,333
I want to be a billboard artist
like Master Pong.

70
00:06:00,875 --> 00:06:03,250
Why do you want to paint billboards?

71
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:06,583
So he can watch movies for free!

72
00:06:06,791 --> 00:06:08,083
Is that so?

73
00:06:08,166 --> 00:06:10,750
That's right, ma'am. I've been painting
for a while now,

74
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:12,625
so the owner lets me watch movies
for free.

75
00:06:13,125 --> 00:06:14,750
I get to see them for free too.

76
00:06:14,833 --> 00:06:15,708
[Pang's mother] Mmm.

77
00:06:15,916 --> 00:06:17,166
Where did I put my key?

78
00:06:18,041 --> 00:06:20,458
Anyway, what do you want to do
when you grow up, Pang?

79
00:06:21,416 --> 00:06:23,208
I want to be a movie star!

80
00:06:24,708 --> 00:06:26,041
Really?

81
00:06:26,250 --> 00:06:28,666
Why do you want to be a movie star, dear?

82
00:06:28,750 --> 00:06:32,291
So I can see myself painted
on a giant billboard someday!

83
00:06:32,583 --> 00:06:36,333
If you become a movie star,
I'll paint your billboard myself!

84
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:39,375
You have to make sure
it's the biggest one ever, okay?

85
00:06:39,458 --> 00:06:40,875
Definitely. The biggest one ever!

86
00:06:40,958 --> 00:06:41,916
You promise?

87
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:43,916
-I promise!
-[Pang chuckles]

88
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:47,541
HANUMAN VS. 7 ULTRAMAN

89
00:06:55,166 --> 00:06:57,416
PETCH CHIANG KHAN

90
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,583
[boy] Damn, no one to pick on today.

91
00:06:59,666 --> 00:07:01,000
-Yeah, boring!
-Totally.

92
00:07:01,083 --> 00:07:02,416
Look, it's Tukkae!

93
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:05,041
[boy] Get him boys!
Bust a cap in his ass!

94
00:07:05,125 --> 00:07:07,125
[shots firing]

95
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:14,583
[Pang] Those guys like to bully Tukkae

96
00:07:14,666 --> 00:07:16,791
because he doesn't have a mother.

97
00:07:17,125 --> 00:07:18,916
[Pang's mother] That's okay.

98
00:07:19,291 --> 00:07:21,541
He still has his Grandma Sri.

99
00:07:21,625 --> 00:07:23,166
-Grandma Sri!
-[Grandma Sri] Yes?

100
00:07:23,333 --> 00:07:25,416
-Ms. Pao is back!
-[Grandma Sri] Okay!

101
00:07:27,041 --> 00:07:28,291
[Grandma Sri] Hurry up
and finish your dinner!

102
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:30,583
What the hell are you picking at it for?

103
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,000
Grandma.

104
00:07:37,250 --> 00:07:41,291
Why aren't we having dinner
at Miss Pang's house today?

105
00:07:42,916 --> 00:07:45,041
They were just asking to be polite.

106
00:07:46,041 --> 00:07:50,500
But that means you need
to mind your manners

107
00:07:50,583 --> 00:07:52,416
and know your place.

108
00:07:53,041 --> 00:07:56,708
I'm just the maid.

109
00:07:57,041 --> 00:08:01,250
There's no way I can sit at the same table
as the boss. It's not proper.

110
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:04,583
But I'm not their servant, Grandma.

111
00:08:04,666 --> 00:08:05,791
Fool!

112
00:08:06,875 --> 00:08:08,375
You are my grandson!

113
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:10,333
And another thing,

114
00:08:10,416 --> 00:08:11,916
when you play with Miss Pang,

115
00:08:12,416 --> 00:08:16,041
you see she doesn't seem
to care where you come from,

116
00:08:16,125 --> 00:08:18,958
but you need to mind your manners
and be aware of your proper place.

117
00:08:19,041 --> 00:08:21,625
Do you understand what that means?

118
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:23,125
I don't understand.

119
00:08:23,375 --> 00:08:24,416
[Grandma Sri groans]

120
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:26,916
That's why you got a stupid name! Tukkae!

121
00:08:31,791 --> 00:08:32,833
Grandma?

122
00:08:32,958 --> 00:08:34,166
Now what?

123
00:08:34,583 --> 00:08:36,833
Why am I named after a gecko?

124
00:08:36,916 --> 00:08:39,083
How would I know?

125
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:41,083
Your mother was the one
who picked it for you.

126
00:08:42,791 --> 00:08:45,541
Where is she now?

127
00:08:46,083 --> 00:08:48,750
I've told you many times
never to ask me about that.

128
00:08:55,625 --> 00:09:00,583
But all the kids at school make fun of me,
calling me "No-Mother Boy."

129
00:09:00,791 --> 00:09:02,750
I just want them to know

130
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:05,375
that I have a mother too.

131
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:11,166
I don't know

132
00:09:12,166 --> 00:09:13,500
where your mother is now.

133
00:09:14,583 --> 00:09:16,416
All I know is, when you were born,

134
00:09:17,125 --> 00:09:19,291
she left you with me.

135
00:09:19,958 --> 00:09:23,083
I asked who your father is,

136
00:09:24,875 --> 00:09:26,666
and she didn't even know.

137
00:09:27,625 --> 00:09:31,250
Since then, she left and never came back.

138
00:09:36,666 --> 00:09:39,958
You really want to know
why she named you after a gecko?

139
00:09:40,458 --> 00:09:41,833
Why?

140
00:09:42,208 --> 00:09:44,458
Because she hates geckos!

141
00:09:51,666 --> 00:09:52,875
Now that you know this,

142
00:09:54,666 --> 00:09:56,458
you still want a mother?

143
00:09:57,541 --> 00:09:58,625
No.

144
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:05,041
If you're not going to eat,
go wash your plate. Go!

145
00:10:21,083 --> 00:10:22,500
Grandma?

146
00:10:23,708 --> 00:10:24,916
What is it?

147
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:28,083
Can I please change my name?

148
00:10:30,875 --> 00:10:32,541
What good would that do?

149
00:10:34,958 --> 00:10:37,750
Because my mother hates geckos,

150
00:10:38,291 --> 00:10:41,375
and so do the kids at school.

151
00:10:45,583 --> 00:10:47,041
You don't have to change your name

152
00:10:48,458 --> 00:10:50,583
because I don't hate geckos.

153
00:10:51,416 --> 00:10:53,750
Please don't ever hate me too, Grandma.

154
00:11:04,958 --> 00:11:08,250
-[school bell rings]
-[boys shouting indistinctly]

155
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:20,541
Not bad, No-Mother Boy!

156
00:11:20,625 --> 00:11:22,166
[kids laughing]

157
00:11:22,625 --> 00:11:24,208
[Nawarat] Kampol Sae-ter!

158
00:11:24,291 --> 00:11:26,083
I will tell the teacher on you!

159
00:11:26,166 --> 00:11:27,333
[Kampol] Just try it!

160
00:11:33,875 --> 00:11:34,916
Let me borrow these,

161
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:37,791
so maybe I can be a great artist
like this No-Mother Boy!

162
00:11:37,875 --> 00:11:39,875
[kids laughing]

163
00:11:41,041 --> 00:11:43,291
Those are my pencils.
I don't want you to use them.

164
00:11:43,375 --> 00:11:45,000
If they can use them,

165
00:11:45,083 --> 00:11:46,791
then why can't I?

166
00:11:47,416 --> 00:11:49,250
Because I won't let you.

167
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:50,333
Give them to me!

168
00:11:50,416 --> 00:11:51,958
You can't have them!

169
00:11:52,041 --> 00:11:53,375
Give them to me!

170
00:11:53,458 --> 00:11:54,833
You can't have them!

171
00:11:54,916 --> 00:11:57,166
-Give them to me!
-You can't have them!

172
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:58,333
[Pang falls]

173
00:12:05,416 --> 00:12:07,416
Meena, you're bleeding!

174
00:12:12,416 --> 00:12:14,291
It's your own fault.

175
00:12:15,166 --> 00:12:16,833
I'm going to tell the teacher!

176
00:12:20,916 --> 00:12:23,541
[teacher] What are you looking at?

177
00:12:23,625 --> 00:12:25,333
Get back in your seats right now!

178
00:12:29,166 --> 00:12:32,041
What's going on in here?

179
00:12:32,125 --> 00:12:34,250
[Kampol] Teacher, help me please!

180
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:37,625
You are all nothing but trouble!

181
00:12:38,125 --> 00:12:40,166
Oh, my! Meena!

182
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:42,166
Blood! I'm going to faint.

183
00:12:43,208 --> 00:12:47,958
-Nawarat! Take her to see the nurse.
-[Kampol whimpering]

184
00:12:50,125 --> 00:12:53,750
You! Mana! Let go of Kampol right now!

185
00:12:53,833 --> 00:12:57,125
You won't let go? You won't let go?

186
00:12:57,208 --> 00:12:59,625
[Kampol] Please don't hit him, teacher.

187
00:12:59,708 --> 00:13:01,708
It's making him bite harder.

188
00:13:03,375 --> 00:13:05,083
Let go of him. Did you hear me?

189
00:13:05,416 --> 00:13:06,708
Let go now!

190
00:13:07,041 --> 00:13:09,250
Oh, my! So much blood!

191
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:10,541
Oh!

192
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:13,541
[Kampol whimpering]

193
00:13:14,166 --> 00:13:17,583
You three! Don't just stand there.
Do something!

194
00:13:18,083 --> 00:13:20,166
[yells louder]

195
00:13:21,666 --> 00:13:24,375
Shit, Tukkae! Why won't you let me go?

196
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,416
My grandma says

197
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:28,458
that if a gecko bites you,

198
00:13:28,541 --> 00:13:31,708
you have to wait for lightning to strike
before it'll let you go.

199
00:13:31,791 --> 00:13:33,875
I hope lightning strikes your grandma.

200
00:13:33,958 --> 00:13:36,125
How long will that be?

201
00:13:36,625 --> 00:13:38,083
Mr. Tukkae, sir.

202
00:13:38,333 --> 00:13:41,291
Please let me go. I give up.

203
00:13:41,833 --> 00:13:43,333
[Tukkae] Say you're sorry now.

204
00:13:43,708 --> 00:13:45,375
What the hell did he say?

205
00:13:45,708 --> 00:13:48,250
He said to say you're sorry.

206
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:49,708
Can't you hear him?

207
00:13:49,791 --> 00:13:51,166
Of course I can!

208
00:13:51,791 --> 00:13:53,958
He's talking into my back.

209
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:56,083
[yells louder]

210
00:13:56,375 --> 00:13:59,083
Mr. Tukkae, sir. I am sorry.

211
00:13:59,458 --> 00:14:01,666
I apologize for everything.

212
00:14:01,750 --> 00:14:02,750
[Tukkae] You sure?

213
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,666
Yes.

214
00:14:05,125 --> 00:14:07,375
Now you know!

215
00:14:09,666 --> 00:14:10,875
[boy] Fat-ass!

216
00:14:18,583 --> 00:14:19,500
[gasps]

217
00:14:25,208 --> 00:14:26,125
[gasps]

218
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:27,916
[teacher] Blood!

219
00:14:30,291 --> 00:14:31,791
[boys scream]

220
00:14:38,625 --> 00:14:43,625
THE ROWDY YEARS

221
00:14:50,916 --> 00:14:55,250
♪ So lovely whenever you are near ♪

222
00:14:55,458 --> 00:15:00,750
♪ Your heart
Sweeter than anyone anywhere ♪

223
00:15:01,541 --> 00:15:05,875
♪ To show how I feel, I do not dare ♪

224
00:15:06,041 --> 00:15:11,458
♪ Can you commence our love affair? ♪

225
00:15:12,208 --> 00:15:16,208
♪ Just a whisper will ♪

226
00:15:16,291 --> 00:15:22,166
♪ Make my spirit soar ♪

227
00:15:22,791 --> 00:15:26,916
♪ Oh, how you make my heart pound ♪

228
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:32,916
♪ The sight of you sets 
My soul spinning round ♪

229
00:15:33,416 --> 00:15:38,958
♪ The fear we can never be ♪

230
00:15:39,041 --> 00:15:43,791
♪ Sends me crashing to the ground ♪

231
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:49,708
♪ Oh, love, show me the way
Build me a bridge to her heart ♪

232
00:15:49,791 --> 00:15:53,958
SINGING LESSONS

233
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:58,791
♪ That I may find a way to know her ♪

234
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:04,125
♪ Never think to part ♪

235
00:16:05,208 --> 00:16:09,583
♪ Dawn to day
Dusk to evening ♪

236
00:16:09,666 --> 00:16:15,541
♪ My love will endure ♪

237
00:16:22,833 --> 00:16:24,125
For 50 satang,

238
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:25,916
-you can watch it for three minutes.
-[honks horn]

239
00:16:37,125 --> 00:16:39,041
[Pang] Are any of these ViewMasters
for sale?

240
00:16:39,125 --> 00:16:40,083
[man] No.

241
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:43,125
[Tukkae] You want one?

242
00:16:44,083 --> 00:16:46,125
[Pang] What about you, Tukkae?

243
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:47,208
[Tukkae] Yes.

244
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:50,750
Uncle, you really won't sell one?

245
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:52,083
[man] I'm sorry. They're not for sale.

246
00:16:52,166 --> 00:16:54,333
-[Tukkae] What about for 100 baht?
-[honks horn]

247
00:16:54,416 --> 00:16:55,416
Time's up, kids.

248
00:16:56,375 --> 00:16:57,958
Too bad!

249
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:17,708
[woman] Cap guns are five baht each.

250
00:17:33,166 --> 00:17:35,000
[Pang] Tukkae, come look at this!

251
00:17:36,041 --> 00:17:37,166
What is it?

252
00:17:39,333 --> 00:17:42,500
[Pang] What kind of candy is this?
Looks so yummy.

253
00:17:43,666 --> 00:17:45,208
They're called jingjok candy.

254
00:17:46,625 --> 00:17:48,333
Come on, kids. Time to go.

255
00:17:48,416 --> 00:17:51,458
Mommy, I want some jingjok candy.

256
00:17:51,541 --> 00:17:52,833
[Pang's mother] What is it?

257
00:17:54,458 --> 00:17:56,833
No, those have artificial coloring.

258
00:17:57,125 --> 00:18:01,041
It will give you a stomach ache.

259
00:18:01,125 --> 00:18:02,333
[Pang] But I want to try it.

260
00:18:02,458 --> 00:18:05,541
[Pang's mother] I bought you fruit.
You can have that when we get home.

261
00:18:09,958 --> 00:18:10,958
Grandma,

262
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:13,375
can I have four baht?

263
00:18:13,708 --> 00:18:14,875
[Grandma Sri] Forget it!

264
00:18:32,625 --> 00:18:33,833
[Pang] Tukkae!

265
00:18:36,291 --> 00:18:37,500
Where are you going?

266
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:40,833
I'm going to collect some bottles to sell.

267
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,541
Can I help?

268
00:18:43,291 --> 00:18:45,416
Sure! Whatever we make,

269
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:47,208
I'll split with you.

270
00:18:47,291 --> 00:18:49,583
Then we can go buy some jingjok candy.

271
00:18:49,666 --> 00:18:50,583
Really?

272
00:18:50,666 --> 00:18:52,000
For real!

273
00:18:52,125 --> 00:18:53,083
Let's go then!

274
00:19:26,416 --> 00:19:28,916
And where are you going to go sell these?

275
00:19:29,166 --> 00:19:30,958
At Uncle Chai's shop.

276
00:19:31,041 --> 00:19:33,750
Oh, you're gonna be rich.

277
00:19:33,833 --> 00:19:36,208
So what are you going to do
with all that cash?

278
00:19:36,291 --> 00:19:38,125
Tukkae is going to buy a cap gun.

279
00:19:38,583 --> 00:19:40,291
And jingjok candy too.

280
00:19:40,416 --> 00:19:41,583
Yes! Let's go.

281
00:19:41,666 --> 00:19:44,083
[Pong] Be careful then.

282
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,291
Look, Tukkae! More bottles.

283
00:20:09,125 --> 00:20:11,208
Altogether, that's four baht.

284
00:20:16,208 --> 00:20:19,083
-Only four baht, Uncle?
-But there are so many bottles.

285
00:20:19,166 --> 00:20:21,458
Fish sauce bottles are 25 satang each.

286
00:20:21,875 --> 00:20:24,875
The rest, I can't use.
Take them back with you.

287
00:20:27,875 --> 00:20:29,166
How much is the cap gun?

288
00:20:29,791 --> 00:20:30,916
Five baht.

289
00:20:31,750 --> 00:20:33,000
[woman] For four baht,
you can have this one.

290
00:20:33,083 --> 00:20:34,291
Plus some free caps.

291
00:20:35,916 --> 00:20:38,041
It looks cool. And it's cheap too!

292
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:43,916
Can I have it for three baht?
I don't need caps.

293
00:20:44,166 --> 00:20:47,125
Why would you want a cap gun
without any caps?

294
00:20:50,041 --> 00:20:52,666
It's okay. I want to save some money

295
00:20:52,750 --> 00:20:54,958
to buy you some jingjok candy.

296
00:20:55,750 --> 00:20:57,166
It's okay. You get your caps.

297
00:20:57,250 --> 00:20:59,208
I can always buy candy another time.

298
00:21:04,458 --> 00:21:07,166
[Kampol] Our gang doesn't allow any girls.

299
00:21:07,750 --> 00:21:08,750
Why not?

300
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:09,833
It's a rule.

301
00:21:10,208 --> 00:21:12,250
What a silly rule!

302
00:21:12,791 --> 00:21:15,416
You have to have a gun to be
in this gang. Do you have one?

303
00:21:18,083 --> 00:21:19,875
I'll go buy one tomorrow.

304
00:21:20,708 --> 00:21:23,875
But you're a girl.
These guns are too loud for you.

305
00:21:25,083 --> 00:21:27,541
If you can stand it, so can I.

306
00:21:30,208 --> 00:21:32,708
We'll have to have a test.

307
00:21:33,708 --> 00:21:34,958
What test?

308
00:21:36,458 --> 00:21:37,791
Shut it!

309
00:21:40,791 --> 00:21:42,541
If you can really stand a gunshot,

310
00:21:42,625 --> 00:21:46,166
then we'll let you be the first girl
in our gang.

311
00:21:46,541 --> 00:21:48,125
What kind of test?

312
00:21:57,958 --> 00:21:58,833
[shot fires]

313
00:22:25,458 --> 00:22:27,541
So Miss Pang isn't back yet?

314
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,125
No, sir.

315
00:22:29,708 --> 00:22:30,791
[boy] Tukkae!

316
00:22:37,416 --> 00:22:38,958
Come play with us!

317
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,958
[shots firing]

318
00:22:46,333 --> 00:22:48,333
[dog barks in distance]

319
00:23:04,833 --> 00:23:07,333
Grandma, has Miss Pang come back yet?

320
00:23:07,625 --> 00:23:09,541
[sighs] Yes,

321
00:23:11,875 --> 00:23:15,833
but she won't be coming
around here anymore.

322
00:23:22,791 --> 00:23:24,208
Why?

323
00:23:25,666 --> 00:23:30,333
Her father was transferred
back to Bangkok for work.

324
00:23:31,875 --> 00:23:35,625
The whole family is going with him.

325
00:23:37,291 --> 00:23:38,291
[sighs]

326
00:23:38,375 --> 00:23:41,500
I just finished helping them pack.

327
00:23:44,291 --> 00:23:46,250
They leave tomorrow,

328
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:50,875
so whatever you gotta do,
do it now, Tukkae.

329
00:23:51,791 --> 00:23:56,541
I don't know when she'll ever be back.

330
00:24:20,208 --> 00:24:23,208
HAPPY NEW YEAR

331
00:24:23,333 --> 00:24:25,291
[indistinct chatter]

332
00:24:27,458 --> 00:24:30,083
Great. Watermelon again!

333
00:24:31,291 --> 00:24:32,875
That's what I got last year.

334
00:24:36,916 --> 00:24:39,666
Don't worry, boss.
Last year, I got a banana.

335
00:24:39,750 --> 00:24:41,458
[all laugh]

336
00:24:43,125 --> 00:24:44,958
Shit, not again!

337
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:56,833
[teacher] Okay, children, listen up!

338
00:24:57,666 --> 00:25:01,916
Meena is leaving our class,

339
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:06,916
so this is the last time
you'll get to see her.

340
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:08,416
Why is that, teacher?

341
00:25:09,250 --> 00:25:13,041
Her family has to move back to Bangkok.

342
00:25:13,208 --> 00:25:16,291
Therefore, before she comes in,

343
00:25:16,375 --> 00:25:21,291
I want everyone to write
a farewell message

344
00:25:21,708 --> 00:25:24,833
to Meena on the chalkboard.

345
00:25:25,333 --> 00:25:27,041
I'll be right back.

346
00:25:29,500 --> 00:25:31,500
This is your last chance, Big Ter.

347
00:25:31,583 --> 00:25:33,416
What the hell are you talking about?

348
00:25:33,500 --> 00:25:35,666
To tell Meena that you like her.

349
00:25:35,750 --> 00:25:37,416
Just write it on the blackboard!

350
00:25:37,875 --> 00:25:40,458
-Yeah.
-How the hell do you know I like her?

351
00:25:40,583 --> 00:25:43,541
[all] Everyone knows!

352
00:25:43,625 --> 00:25:44,625
That's bullshit.

353
00:25:44,708 --> 00:25:46,125
I don't have a crush on her.

354
00:25:46,208 --> 00:25:48,375
Tukkae is the one who is in love with her.

355
00:25:48,458 --> 00:25:52,166
Yeah. That's why you were always
trying to get between them.

356
00:25:52,583 --> 00:25:53,541
Not true!

357
00:25:53,625 --> 00:25:55,291
[all] Really?

358
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:06,291
Has everyone written farewell to Meena?

359
00:26:07,041 --> 00:26:08,208
[Kampol] Not us.

360
00:26:08,291 --> 00:26:10,250
[teacher] And why is that?

361
00:26:11,500 --> 00:26:14,958
We want to sing her a song instead.
May we?

362
00:26:15,041 --> 00:26:16,500
Really?

363
00:26:17,166 --> 00:26:19,625
What are you going to sing for her?

364
00:26:20,458 --> 00:26:22,166
It's called "The Promise,"

365
00:26:22,291 --> 00:26:24,083
written by Big Ter here.

366
00:26:24,416 --> 00:26:26,916
Let me hear it, please.

367
00:26:27,500 --> 00:26:29,583
[boy] One, two...

368
00:26:30,166 --> 00:26:36,583
♪ Before we part, I promise you ♪

369
00:26:37,166 --> 00:26:44,083
♪ A solemn pledge before we meet again ♪

370
00:26:45,041 --> 00:26:50,958
♪ A wave of the hand
A promise from the heart ♪

371
00:26:51,041 --> 00:26:54,916
♪ Because love can never be severed ♪

372
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:58,875
♪ Its ties will last forever ♪

373
00:27:22,750 --> 00:27:25,333
Hey! You forgot your cart.

374
00:27:27,208 --> 00:27:33,000
♪ Before we part, I promise you ♪

375
00:27:33,583 --> 00:27:40,416
♪ A solemn pledge before we meet again ♪

376
00:27:40,958 --> 00:27:46,958
♪ A wave of the hand
A promise from the heart ♪

377
00:27:47,041 --> 00:27:50,500
♪ Because love can never be severed ♪

378
00:27:50,958 --> 00:27:54,041
♪ Its ties will last forever ♪

379
00:27:59,541 --> 00:28:04,250
♪ All the good things
That linger in memories ♪

380
00:28:05,333 --> 00:28:12,250
♪ Though we are apart
You will always be in my heart ♪

381
00:28:12,875 --> 00:28:18,416
♪ Don't forget our promises ♪

382
00:28:18,666 --> 00:28:22,125
♪ For our hearts are strong ♪

383
00:28:22,625 --> 00:28:26,875
♪ Always striving to do good
In this world ♪

384
00:28:31,250 --> 00:28:33,583
[kids applauding]

385
00:28:34,541 --> 00:28:40,125
HAPPY NEW YEAR

386
00:28:52,083 --> 00:28:53,083
[boy] Tukkae!

387
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:55,708
Miss Pang's already left.

388
00:29:00,625 --> 00:29:03,083
DON'T FORGET ME, NAWARAT

389
00:29:15,208 --> 00:29:17,208
[Tukkae panting]

390
00:29:30,125 --> 00:29:33,083
[Grandma Sri] Miss Pang asked me
to give this to you before she left.

391
00:29:38,583 --> 00:29:40,958
Looks like everything worked out
between you two.

392
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:27,833
[typing]

393
00:30:27,916 --> 00:30:31,458
INT. THE PALACE - NIGHT

394
00:30:31,541 --> 00:30:33,541
[dance music playing]

395
00:30:43,416 --> 00:30:44,416
[man] Pang!

396
00:30:45,416 --> 00:30:48,000
How about a drink?

397
00:31:00,958 --> 00:31:02,958
[crowd chanting]

398
00:31:08,250 --> 00:31:09,250
Ple!

399
00:31:45,458 --> 00:31:46,541
Kheng.

400
00:31:46,833 --> 00:31:47,833
Yeah?

401
00:31:48,375 --> 00:31:50,833
Have you ever wanted to be a director?

402
00:31:51,291 --> 00:31:52,958
I've thought about it,

403
00:31:53,541 --> 00:31:56,333
but there's no way.

404
00:31:57,583 --> 00:31:58,666
Why not?

405
00:31:58,750 --> 00:32:02,833
To be a director,
you have to tell a good story.

406
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:05,250
I don't know how to do that.

407
00:32:07,541 --> 00:32:09,458
So if you want to be a director,

408
00:32:09,625 --> 00:32:14,458
the first thing you need to ask yourself
is, "Can I tell a good story?"

409
00:32:16,791 --> 00:32:18,875
What if I think I can do that?

410
00:32:19,541 --> 00:32:21,875
You think you can?

411
00:32:24,875 --> 00:32:26,291
What story would you tell?

412
00:32:29,500 --> 00:32:31,458
[Ple] Again?

413
00:32:32,208 --> 00:32:34,000
This time, it's too much.

414
00:32:34,708 --> 00:32:36,125
How is that?

415
00:32:38,166 --> 00:32:39,791
She kicked me out of the house.

416
00:32:40,416 --> 00:32:42,666
But that's your house.

417
00:32:42,750 --> 00:32:45,625
You were there
before your father married that bitch.

418
00:32:46,041 --> 00:32:49,250
But he left her everything when he died.

419
00:32:49,333 --> 00:32:51,208
How the hell did that happen?

420
00:32:51,500 --> 00:32:54,916
How could your father care
about that bitch more than you?

421
00:32:55,500 --> 00:32:56,416
[Ple sighs]

422
00:32:56,500 --> 00:32:58,625
Maybe I wasn't such a good daughter.

423
00:33:00,416 --> 00:33:03,625
Forget it. What do you need from me?

424
00:33:07,791 --> 00:33:10,125
Can I crash at your place for a bit?

425
00:33:10,416 --> 00:33:11,416
Okay.

426
00:33:12,166 --> 00:33:15,375
Will your boyfriend mind?

427
00:33:15,750 --> 00:33:17,208
I just broke up with him.

428
00:33:17,458 --> 00:33:19,125
You came at the right time, Pang.

429
00:33:19,250 --> 00:33:20,875
Get drunk with me!

430
00:33:20,958 --> 00:33:23,125
Come celebrate my return to single life!

431
00:33:23,333 --> 00:33:25,000
If you say no,

432
00:33:25,083 --> 00:33:27,791
then don't bother coming to stay with me.

433
00:33:28,083 --> 00:33:29,083
Deal?

434
00:33:31,833 --> 00:33:33,166
Okay.

435
00:33:33,708 --> 00:33:35,541
That's what I'm talking about!

436
00:33:42,416 --> 00:33:45,041
Let me buy the next round for you ladies.

437
00:33:56,083 --> 00:33:58,083
[TV playing]

438
00:34:00,875 --> 00:34:03,041
[announcer] On today's edition
of Guess My Life,

439
00:34:03,125 --> 00:34:09,791
I have an individual here who may not be
completely sane for you judging viewers.

440
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:11,500
What's your name?

441
00:34:13,083 --> 00:34:15,041
[man] My name is not important.

442
00:34:15,458 --> 00:34:17,333
Happiness is more important.

443
00:34:17,833 --> 00:34:19,500
[announcer] Yes,
the name is not important.

444
00:34:19,583 --> 00:34:22,458
Ladies and gentlemen,
we have someone who likes to spray.

445
00:34:22,541 --> 00:34:24,250
Spray paint, that is.

446
00:34:24,333 --> 00:34:27,750
Everywhere. Public places,
buses, bus stops, public toilets,

447
00:34:27,875 --> 00:34:30,875
-and...
-[man] the walls of a temple,

448
00:34:31,541 --> 00:34:32,625
people's fences.

449
00:34:32,708 --> 00:34:35,291
If I see a pristine wall,
I can't help myself...

450
00:35:03,916 --> 00:35:05,375
[Kampol] You didn't know her?

451
00:35:06,333 --> 00:35:08,416
Then how did she end up here?

452
00:35:08,666 --> 00:35:09,666
[Kheng] Oh...

453
00:35:11,041 --> 00:35:13,250
It's useless.

454
00:35:13,791 --> 00:35:15,833
You go back, Tukkae.

455
00:35:15,916 --> 00:35:17,625
I'll wait for the mechanic here.

456
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:21,083
[taxi driver] Look over there.

457
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:30,125
Stop the car, please.

458
00:35:45,791 --> 00:35:47,291
[thunder rumbling]

459
00:35:53,791 --> 00:35:55,833
[tires screeching]

460
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:02,625
I saw that she was blind drunk.

461
00:36:07,333 --> 00:36:10,750
She was getting soaked, so I
brought her back here to get changed.

462
00:36:12,791 --> 00:36:14,125
So did you...

463
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:17,583
You asshole! I'm not like you.

464
00:36:17,666 --> 00:36:18,916
You chicken shit!

465
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:22,625
But she probably
thought you were going to.

466
00:36:22,708 --> 00:36:24,500
That's why she smacked you in the face.

467
00:36:24,750 --> 00:36:25,791
Just bad luck.

468
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:30,916
[Pang] I have no idea
how I ended up at that house.

469
00:36:31,875 --> 00:36:35,291
I don't even remember
getting into Ake's car.

470
00:36:35,916 --> 00:36:38,833
Maybe he drugged us?

471
00:36:39,166 --> 00:36:40,666
Do you think that's what happened?

472
00:36:40,750 --> 00:36:41,666
Definitely.

473
00:36:41,750 --> 00:36:44,666
I've never been that wasted before
in my life.

474
00:36:44,750 --> 00:36:47,666
I remember looking for you.

475
00:36:47,916 --> 00:36:49,791
The next thing I remember

476
00:36:49,875 --> 00:36:52,083
is the security guard waking me up.

477
00:36:52,166 --> 00:36:54,666
I don't know
when I passed out in the bathroom.

478
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:59,291
Those guys must have been
Ake's gang for sure.

479
00:36:59,791 --> 00:37:01,416
Should we go to the police?

480
00:37:07,125 --> 00:37:09,916
Forget it. I went to get
checked out by the doctor.

481
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,583
He said nothing happened to me.

482
00:37:12,291 --> 00:37:14,875
You want me to send some
Army boys to rough them up?

483
00:37:15,208 --> 00:37:16,958
You're going to tell your father?

484
00:37:17,041 --> 00:37:21,458
No way! But I can tell Pued and Padd
to go beat the shit out of them.

485
00:37:25,333 --> 00:37:26,333
MAE NAK 3001: GHOST ODYSSEY

486
00:37:26,416 --> 00:37:28,083
[Tukkae] Tong,
what did you think of that movie?

487
00:37:28,833 --> 00:37:30,041
[Tong] I didn't enjoy it.

488
00:37:31,083 --> 00:37:34,250
[Tukkae] But everyone else
was laughing the whole time.

489
00:37:34,666 --> 00:37:36,291
That's other people, not me.

490
00:37:36,375 --> 00:37:38,000
You were asking my opinion, right?

491
00:37:47,541 --> 00:37:48,458
[camera shutter clicking]

492
00:37:53,208 --> 00:37:57,166
So are you making your movie, Tukkae?

493
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:00,666
I'm not making a movie.

494
00:38:01,458 --> 00:38:03,000
I'm making a story.

495
00:38:05,041 --> 00:38:06,500
Story for your movie?

496
00:38:07,041 --> 00:38:08,083
That's right.

497
00:38:08,916 --> 00:38:10,208
You said it yourself,

498
00:38:10,583 --> 00:38:14,000
if I'm going to direct,
I have to have a story to tell.

499
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:15,500
Oh,

500
00:38:17,916 --> 00:38:19,250
about the art students?

501
00:38:19,708 --> 00:38:22,000
Yes, it's about my friends.

502
00:38:22,291 --> 00:38:24,375
And how are you going to tell this story?

503
00:38:25,041 --> 00:38:27,583
I'm going to take these photos

504
00:38:28,041 --> 00:38:31,208
and use them to build a new story.

505
00:38:31,916 --> 00:38:33,291
A whole new story?

506
00:38:33,833 --> 00:38:34,833
Right.

507
00:38:36,791 --> 00:38:37,791
A teen movie?

508
00:38:39,125 --> 00:38:40,333
A romance.

509
00:38:40,583 --> 00:38:41,583
Oh!

510
00:38:48,125 --> 00:38:51,291
So how long do you plan
to work at Jom's shop?

511
00:38:52,458 --> 00:38:54,541
[Ple] I don't know. A while, I guess.

512
00:38:56,041 --> 00:38:58,000
I don't feel like thinking too far ahead.

513
00:39:04,625 --> 00:39:07,458
Excuse me. I want to rent costumes
for a commercial shoot.

514
00:39:07,541 --> 00:39:09,166
Who should I talk to?

515
00:39:09,666 --> 00:39:13,250
You can leave a name card.
Someone will get back to you.

516
00:39:13,500 --> 00:39:14,541
Okay.

517
00:39:17,375 --> 00:39:18,375
Here you go.

518
00:39:21,750 --> 00:39:23,541
Nawarat Meesukhon?

519
00:39:24,166 --> 00:39:25,208
That's right.

520
00:39:27,208 --> 00:39:28,458
Do you remember me?

521
00:39:30,916 --> 00:39:32,458
You are...

522
00:39:32,541 --> 00:39:34,083
It's me, Pang!

523
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:41,583
Pang? Meena Ruksasuk?

524
00:39:41,666 --> 00:39:43,291
I got a degree in pharmacy at Sirirat.

525
00:39:43,666 --> 00:39:44,708
Pharmacy?

526
00:39:44,791 --> 00:39:47,250
Why are you working in commercials?

527
00:39:47,416 --> 00:39:50,708
My boyfriend is an assistant director.

528
00:39:50,958 --> 00:39:52,875
