00:55:47,416 --> 00:55:50,416
I wouldn't have flewed
all the way here if I didn't think so.

786
00:55:50,500 --> 00:55:53,041
I think you mean "flown."

787
00:56:01,708 --> 00:56:03,708
[inaudible]

788
00:56:21,000 --> 00:56:22,333
BAAN NAWK

789
00:56:22,416 --> 00:56:23,666
[in Thai] Car coming.

790
00:56:23,875 --> 00:56:27,125
Stop the car! Happy Songkran!

791
00:56:32,916 --> 00:56:35,541
Get the dude in the glasses! Over there!

792
00:56:39,208 --> 00:56:41,875
Hey, Tukkae!
When does your movie start shooting?

793
00:56:42,458 --> 00:56:43,708
I don't know.

794
00:56:44,166 --> 00:56:48,708
You know what? I read in the news
that your Pang is starring in it.

795
00:56:50,333 --> 00:56:51,333
I know.

796
00:56:51,625 --> 00:56:54,375
I told you, it's not a coincidence.

797
00:56:54,541 --> 00:56:58,208
[Kampol] Enough with that bullshit,
Mr. Movie Critic!

798
00:57:22,708 --> 00:57:23,708
[John] This way, please.

799
00:57:26,125 --> 00:57:27,166
First AD!

800
00:57:27,333 --> 00:57:28,375
Yes?

801
00:57:32,166 --> 00:57:33,833
Take our star to makeup.

802
00:57:34,958 --> 00:57:35,958
[May] See you.

803
00:57:37,083 --> 00:57:38,208
This way, please.

804
00:57:39,083 --> 00:57:42,208
[John] Hey, kid,
give me a copy of the script.

805
00:57:46,500 --> 00:57:48,625
Jong, our leading lady
is here to do her makeup.

806
00:57:48,791 --> 00:57:49,958
Hello, Jong.

807
00:57:51,583 --> 00:57:53,000
Have you been waiting long, Ple?

808
00:57:53,250 --> 00:57:54,500
Where did you go?

809
00:57:55,583 --> 00:57:57,291
I was with John.

810
00:57:58,583 --> 00:58:02,333
Excuse me, John? Which scene
would you like for the screen test?

811
00:58:02,916 --> 00:58:04,166
One of the romantic ones.

812
00:58:04,791 --> 00:58:05,958
Really?

813
00:58:06,750 --> 00:58:09,708
But we need to find someone
to play opposite Pang.

814
00:58:10,833 --> 00:58:13,708
Then use Tukkae. He knows the script.

815
00:58:15,041 --> 00:58:18,583
Pang, we're going
to rehearse scene 69 now.

816
00:58:19,125 --> 00:58:20,125
Okay.

817
00:58:20,208 --> 00:58:21,375
You want me to act?

818
00:58:21,458 --> 00:58:24,333
Yeah, just as a stand-in
for the lead actor.

819
00:58:24,416 --> 00:58:25,583
Really? The lead actor?

820
00:58:25,666 --> 00:58:27,833
Yes, you better start practicing
your lines.

821
00:58:29,041 --> 00:58:32,666
Wait. You don't need to practice.
You wrote the damn thing, right?

822
00:58:46,083 --> 00:58:47,875
John, Pang is here.

823
00:58:50,083 --> 00:58:54,291
[John] Okay, Pang, today, don't worry
about getting all your lines right.

824
00:58:54,416 --> 00:58:57,875
I'm just testing camera angles.

825
00:58:59,125 --> 00:59:01,375
-Okay.
-Clear!

826
00:59:01,500 --> 00:59:03,666
This way please, Pang.

827
00:59:03,875 --> 00:59:04,875
[Pang] Okay.

828
00:59:06,125 --> 00:59:09,708
I have someone here
who will read Puen's lines for you.

829
00:59:10,208 --> 00:59:11,458
Assistant! Come here!

830
00:59:13,500 --> 00:59:15,875
If our two actors are ready, let us know.

831
00:59:38,333 --> 00:59:39,750
[Pang] Can I have a moment please?

832
00:59:48,000 --> 00:59:50,291
You want me to call Pued and Padd
to take care of him?

833
00:59:52,583 --> 00:59:53,625
What do you think?

834
00:59:54,583 --> 00:59:56,416
No, I don't think that's necessary.

835
01:00:02,458 --> 01:00:04,000
Can we have a minute?

836
01:00:09,625 --> 01:00:10,916
I want to talk to you.

837
01:00:23,916 --> 01:00:25,833
They must be practicing lines, right?

838
01:00:27,916 --> 01:00:28,958
[May] I guess so.

839
01:00:32,541 --> 01:00:33,500
[Tukkae] Miss Pang--

840
01:00:33,583 --> 01:00:36,000
I don't want to know
what happened at your house.

841
01:00:36,833 --> 01:00:38,583
I just want to forget all about it.

842
01:00:39,083 --> 01:00:41,041
I want you to forget what happened too.

843
01:00:42,333 --> 01:00:44,208
Forget everything about that night.

844
01:00:45,000 --> 01:00:46,666
Forget that you ever saw me.

845
01:00:47,958 --> 01:00:50,250
But actually, that night--

846
01:00:50,333 --> 01:00:51,833
That night we never met.

847
01:00:53,583 --> 01:00:56,541
We don't know each other.

848
01:01:00,416 --> 01:01:02,416
I don't want to have anything else
to do with you.

849
01:01:06,083 --> 01:01:07,208
Okay, fine.

850
01:01:18,541 --> 01:01:19,541
I'm ready.

851
01:01:20,125 --> 01:01:22,791
-Are you ready?
-[Tukkae] Yes.

852
01:01:22,875 --> 01:01:25,083
When I say action,
you two come into frame.

853
01:01:25,208 --> 01:01:26,333
Is the camera ready?

854
01:01:26,583 --> 01:01:28,000
-[cameraman] Ready.
-Lights!

855
01:01:29,625 --> 01:01:30,458
"CLOSER THAN FRIENDS"

856
01:01:30,541 --> 01:01:31,583
[man] Camera!

857
01:01:32,041 --> 01:01:33,125
[cameraman] Rolling!

858
01:01:33,500 --> 01:01:34,500
[John] Action!

859
01:01:48,250 --> 01:01:49,916
Puen, why did you do that?

860
01:01:56,375 --> 01:01:57,416
I'm sorry.

861
01:01:58,541 --> 01:01:59,875
I didn't mean it, Prim.

862
01:02:04,333 --> 01:02:05,375
That night,

863
01:02:06,750 --> 01:02:07,916
I was drunk.

864
01:02:13,500 --> 01:02:15,666
-[John] May.
-Yes?

865
01:02:15,833 --> 01:02:17,333
This kid isn't half bad, is he?

866
01:02:25,125 --> 01:02:28,041
[sobbing] Puen, don't you know
how much she loved you?

867
01:02:29,541 --> 01:02:30,583
Miss Pang,

868
01:02:32,208 --> 01:02:33,583
I think that maybe you should--

869
01:02:34,458 --> 01:02:36,208
My name is Prim.

870
01:02:38,208 --> 01:02:39,500
[sniffles]

871
01:02:42,916 --> 01:02:44,916
John, can I talk to you for a minute?

872
01:02:46,666 --> 01:02:47,833
Should I say cut, sir?

873
01:02:47,916 --> 01:02:48,916
Obviously.

874
01:02:53,291 --> 01:02:55,333
The assistant
who is reading lines with me...

875
01:02:56,041 --> 01:02:57,083
Yes? What about him?

876
01:02:58,041 --> 01:03:00,083
Would it be okay if he was not around?
Ever?

877
01:03:02,125 --> 01:03:04,375
So no one from Sunny Films
has contacted you at all?

878
01:03:06,625 --> 01:03:07,625
[Tukkae] No.

879
01:03:09,000 --> 01:03:11,166
I think you should just go there yourself.

880
01:03:11,958 --> 01:03:14,666
And tell them,
if they're going to fire you like this,

881
01:03:14,750 --> 01:03:16,208
then you want your script back.

882
01:03:17,625 --> 01:03:19,916
I don't think
we can give you back your script.

883
01:03:20,791 --> 01:03:21,833
Why not?

884
01:03:25,708 --> 01:03:26,833
[woman] Have a look.

885
01:03:31,625 --> 01:03:34,625
It says so right here
in the contract you signed.

886
01:03:34,916 --> 01:03:38,750
You are an employee.
And the law is on the employer's side.

887
01:03:39,291 --> 01:03:42,625
Frankly, you don't have any right
to get it back.

888
01:03:43,625 --> 01:03:46,666
We don't know
what happened between you and Pang.

889
01:03:46,833 --> 01:03:49,166
We just want everything to end peacefully.

890
01:03:55,458 --> 01:03:56,458
[door shuts]

891
01:04:01,375 --> 01:04:02,375
[man] Hey!

892
01:04:07,708 --> 01:04:09,041
[dogs barking in distance]

893
01:04:25,500 --> 01:04:30,958
EXT. CHIANG KHAN - DAY

894
01:04:44,375 --> 01:04:50,666
LESS SLACK, MORE LIVELY.

895
01:04:59,958 --> 01:05:02,458
PETCH CHIANG KHAN

896
01:05:02,541 --> 01:05:04,708
PONG POSTER

897
01:05:06,458 --> 01:05:10,041
[Ong] This is the last billboard

898
01:05:10,375 --> 01:05:12,041
that Pong painted for me.

899
01:05:12,541 --> 01:05:13,541
Hello, Uncle Ong.

900
01:05:16,625 --> 01:05:19,000
Pong has lung cancer now.

901
01:05:19,083 --> 01:05:22,583
You have to find someone else
to draw a movie poster.

902
01:05:23,000 --> 01:05:25,000
I'm not doing movies anymore, Uncle Ong.

903
01:05:25,750 --> 01:05:28,833
Really? So what are you doing now?

904
01:05:31,208 --> 01:05:34,250
I'm a cartoonist for a humor rag.

905
01:05:36,083 --> 01:05:37,166
A cartoonist?

906
01:05:44,041 --> 01:05:46,208
[doctor] How long will you be
staying in town?

907
01:05:46,291 --> 01:05:48,541
[Tukkae] I think it will be
for a while, Doctor.

908
01:05:49,791 --> 01:05:52,833
[doctor] Grandma Sri, look who's here
to see you. It's your grandson.

909
01:05:58,166 --> 01:05:59,250
Hello, Grandma.

910
01:06:02,125 --> 01:06:03,125
It's me, Tukkae.

911
01:06:04,750 --> 01:06:05,833
Tukkae!

912
01:06:06,000 --> 01:06:08,500
-Have you eaten anything yet?
-Not yet.

913
01:06:08,583 --> 01:06:10,791
Why not?

914
01:06:11,083 --> 01:06:14,000
You know the only luck that matters
is having enough to eat.

915
01:06:15,458 --> 01:06:17,666
[doctor] Excuse me, Tukkae.
I have to do my rounds.

916
01:06:17,875 --> 01:06:19,416
Make yourself at home.

917
01:06:28,500 --> 01:06:33,291
-Tukkae! Have you eaten anything yet?
-Not yet.

918
01:06:33,375 --> 01:06:35,291
Why not?

919
01:06:35,541 --> 01:06:38,041
You know the only luck that matters
is having enough to eat.

920
01:07:20,875 --> 01:07:22,250
Why don't you shoot?

921
01:07:24,083 --> 01:07:26,041
Let the new guy do it.

922
01:07:27,291 --> 01:07:28,333
Tukkae.

923
01:07:31,666 --> 01:07:32,958
If you don't do it,

924
01:07:33,833 --> 01:07:36,125
you can't be in our gang.

925
01:07:38,166 --> 01:07:39,875
[Pang] Tukkae, let's go home.

926
01:07:39,958 --> 01:07:43,250
I don't want to play
with these little creeps.

927
01:07:43,333 --> 01:07:44,833
[Kampol] Yeah, run along!

928
01:07:44,916 --> 01:07:48,833
We don't want any lady boys
in our gang anyway.

929
01:07:53,208 --> 01:07:54,250
I'll do it.

930
01:07:54,333 --> 01:07:55,875
That's what I'm talking about.

931
01:08:09,291 --> 01:08:10,291
Do it!

932
01:08:11,416 --> 01:08:12,416
Shoot her!

933
01:08:55,208 --> 01:08:56,375
[John] Ladies and gentlemen,

934
01:08:57,500 --> 01:09:03,500
I have had the privilege
of working with many actresses,

935
01:09:04,625 --> 01:09:08,750
but this young lady
is really something special.

936
01:09:09,583 --> 01:09:12,416
Aside from being a great actress,

937
01:09:12,625 --> 01:09:16,333
she is also a gifted singer as well.

938
01:09:17,166 --> 01:09:21,083
If you have a chance to hear her sing,

939
01:09:21,500 --> 01:09:23,958
then I am certain that you
will fall in love with her too.

940
01:09:24,041 --> 01:09:25,750
Please welcome Pang to the stage.

941
01:09:26,625 --> 01:09:28,625
[audience clapping and cheering]

942
01:09:32,083 --> 01:09:33,500
[music playing]

943
01:09:47,250 --> 01:09:51,791
♪ So lovely whenever you are near ♪

944
01:09:51,916 --> 01:09:57,416
♪ Your heart
Sweeter than anyone anywhere ♪

945
01:09:57,916 --> 01:10:02,291
♪ To show how I feel, I do not dare ♪

946
01:10:02,375 --> 01:10:08,791
♪ Can you begin our love affair? ♪

947
01:10:08,916 --> 01:10:13,083
♪ Just a whisper will ♪

948
01:10:13,166 --> 01:10:19,166
♪ Make my spirit soar ♪

949
01:10:19,500 --> 01:10:24,208
♪ Oh, how you make my heart pound ♪

950
01:10:24,291 --> 01:10:30,250
♪ The sight of you sets
My soul spinning round ♪

951
01:10:30,416 --> 01:10:35,541
♪ The fear we can never be ♪

952
01:10:35,625 --> 01:10:40,791
♪ Sends me crashing to the ground ♪

953
01:10:41,000 --> 01:10:46,083
♪ Oh, love, show me the way ♪

954
01:10:46,166 --> 01:10:51,583
♪ Build me a bridge to her heart ♪

955
01:10:51,875 --> 01:10:56,333
♪ That I may find a way to know her ♪

956
01:10:56,416 --> 01:11:02,166
♪ Never think to part ♪

957
01:11:02,250 --> 01:11:07,000
♪ Dawn to day
Dusk to evening ♪

958
01:11:07,083 --> 01:11:13,583
♪ My love will endure ♪

959
01:11:13,958 --> 01:11:17,208
You always said you wanted to make movies

960
01:11:17,875 --> 01:11:23,500
and that, someday, we would show
one of your movies right here.

961
01:11:23,583 --> 01:11:24,791
Don't you remember?

962
01:11:27,041 --> 01:11:28,833
I tried, Uncle Ong.

963
01:11:29,166 --> 01:11:32,875
So now that dream will never come true?

964
01:11:39,250 --> 01:11:40,500
[kids giggling]

965
01:11:46,000 --> 01:11:48,083
[man] So I heard
you studied art in school?

966
01:11:48,333 --> 01:11:49,250
[Tukkae] That's right.

967
01:11:50,041 --> 01:11:52,833
So have you seen that movie
Closer Than Friends yet?

968
01:11:54,666 --> 01:11:55,750
Not yet.

969
01:11:55,833 --> 01:11:58,916
[exclaims] The actress in that one
is amazing.

970
01:11:59,583 --> 01:12:02,708
It's hard to believe
it was only her first movie.

971
01:12:03,333 --> 01:12:06,833
But I heard she got special attention
from the director.

972
01:12:08,416 --> 01:12:12,875
Rumor has it,
the two of them fell in love on set.

973
01:12:12,958 --> 01:12:14,958
CLOSER THAN FRIENDS

974
01:12:29,500 --> 01:12:31,083
[phone ringing]

975
01:12:34,458 --> 01:12:36,291
-Hello?
-[Tukkae] Hello.

976
01:12:37,208 --> 01:12:38,583
May I speak to Miss Pang?

977
01:12:38,750 --> 01:12:39,875
Who is this?

978
01:12:42,041 --> 01:12:44,416
An old friend. My name is Tukkae.

979
01:12:47,041 --> 01:12:48,416
-Pang?
-Hmm?

980
01:12:48,500 --> 01:12:50,416
Do you know someone named Tukkae?

981
01:12:55,041 --> 01:12:56,083
[Pang] Hello?

982
01:12:56,416 --> 01:12:57,625
Hello, Miss Pang.

983
01:12:59,291 --> 01:13:00,333
Tukkae?

984
01:13:02,625 --> 01:13:03,625
Yes.

985
01:13:04,583 --> 01:13:06,583
Tukkae, Mana Jitmankong?

986
01:13:09,708 --> 01:13:10,750
That's right.

987
01:13:12,500 --> 01:13:15,541
How did you get my number?

988
01:13:18,833 --> 01:13:21,791
It wasn't that hard.
You're quite famous these days.

989
01:13:22,833 --> 01:13:24,500
Oh, please.

990
01:13:24,708 --> 01:13:27,291
Anyway, how long has it been?

991
01:13:28,000 --> 01:13:30,583
How is your Grandma?

992
01:13:34,000 --> 01:13:36,875
Grandma Sri has dementia.

993
01:13:37,708 --> 01:13:40,750
She's staying at the hospital now.

994
01:13:42,541 --> 01:13:44,041
Which hospital?

995
01:13:45,708 --> 01:13:46,875
In Loei.

996
01:13:48,416 --> 01:13:50,041
But she's healthy and happy.

997
01:13:53,000 --> 01:13:54,833
What about Master Pong and Uncle Ong?

998
01:13:57,666 --> 01:13:59,083
Master Pong passed away.

999
01:14:00,166 --> 01:14:01,166
Really?

1000
01:14:02,250 --> 01:14:04,583
But Uncle Ong is well.

1001
01:14:05,708 --> 01:14:07,833
Is he still running the projectors?

1002
01:14:08,375 --> 01:14:10,500
Yes, same as usual.

1003
01:14:13,541 --> 01:14:14,833
Unbelievable!

1004
01:14:16,000 --> 01:14:18,458
So why are you calling me?

1005
01:14:24,041 --> 01:14:28,208
I wanted to say sorry about that day.

1006
01:14:29,625 --> 01:14:30,791
Which day?

1007
01:14:32,000 --> 01:14:33,208
The day I...

1008
01:14:36,041 --> 01:14:38,375
I shot that cap gun at you.

1009
01:14:40,250 --> 01:14:41,583
Oh, Tukkae!

1010
01:14:42,000 --> 01:14:44,291
I was never mad at you.

1011
01:14:45,000 --> 01:14:47,750
Didn't you get my present?

1012
01:14:56,958 --> 01:14:58,000
I did.

1013
01:14:59,708 --> 01:15:01,583
I still have it.

1014
01:15:05,041 --> 01:15:07,791
So you should have known
I was never mad at you.

1015
01:15:17,208 --> 01:15:18,916
Thank you very much, Miss Pang.

1016
01:15:19,208 --> 01:15:20,458
[sniffles softly]

1017
01:15:21,250 --> 01:15:24,916
Look, you can stop calling me
Miss Pang already.

1018
01:15:25,208 --> 01:15:26,416
[chuckles]

1019
01:15:26,500 --> 01:15:27,666
Okay.

1020
01:15:31,333 --> 01:15:33,083
Actually, I'm glad you called.

1021
01:15:33,666 --> 01:15:35,000
Are you free next week?

1022
01:15:36,000 --> 01:15:37,083
Yes.

1023
01:15:39,791 --> 01:15:41,458
I want to send you an invitation.

1024
01:15:42,708 --> 01:15:43,791
Invitation to what?

1025
01:16:00,000 --> 01:16:01,416
[inaudible]

1026
01:16:21,541 --> 01:16:22,541
TUKKAE

1027
01:16:29,375 --> 01:16:33,166
-[Kheng] Hey, is the boss in?
-[man] Yeah, he's upstairs.

1028
01:16:33,250 --> 01:16:34,416
-[Kheng] Upstairs?
-[man] Yes.

1029
01:16:34,750 --> 01:16:36,625
So how do you know this producer?

1030
01:16:37,000 --> 01:16:39,416
I designed a logo for him once.

1031
01:16:44,583 --> 01:16:45,708
[producer sighs]

1032
01:16:46,333 --> 01:16:47,333
[chuckles]

1033
01:16:47,416 --> 01:16:49,416
[producer] Another thing,

1034
01:16:49,500 --> 01:16:54,541
whenever you write the script,

1035
01:16:54,625 --> 01:16:56,708
I want a cat.

1036
01:16:56,791 --> 01:16:59,208
-"Cast"?
-"Cat," "cast," same difference,

1037
01:16:59,958 --> 01:17:05,250
I just want some big ones.

1038
01:17:06,000 --> 01:17:08,291
Do you mean "boobs"?

1039
01:17:08,375 --> 01:17:09,916
Watch your mouth!

1040
01:17:10,000 --> 01:17:13,333
Kids can't hear that kind of language.

1041
01:17:13,625 --> 01:17:16,083
So you want to make a kids' movie?

1042
01:17:16,166 --> 01:17:18,500
It's not for kids.

1043
01:17:18,708 --> 01:17:20,583
For adults!

1044
