Why did you pick Pang
to be your lead actress?

1300
01:39:15,416 --> 01:39:18,041
Because there is no one better suited
for the role than her.

1301
01:39:19,125 --> 01:39:21,458
Is it also
because you are in a relationship?

1302
01:39:21,541 --> 01:39:22,875
[press members murmuring]

1303
01:39:24,958 --> 01:39:27,125
I can't lie and say that was not a factor.

1304
01:39:27,208 --> 01:39:28,416
I knew it.

1305
01:39:30,000 --> 01:39:32,000
[reporter] So the reason
you cast Ms. Pang Meena

1306
01:39:32,083 --> 01:39:33,750
is because of your romantic relationship?

1307
01:39:33,833 --> 01:39:35,916
And because she is perfect for the role.

1308
01:39:37,541 --> 01:39:39,666
[Ple] But don't you already have a wife?

1309
01:39:44,083 --> 01:39:45,875
[John] I'm glad you asked that question.

1310
01:39:47,333 --> 01:39:49,708
We already have a divorce.

1311
01:39:49,791 --> 01:39:51,208
[press members murmuring]

1312
01:39:55,833 --> 01:40:00,583
I have this divorce certificate here
because I want everyone to know

1313
01:40:00,958 --> 01:40:02,333
that Pang did nothing wrong.

1314
01:40:05,166 --> 01:40:08,250
What happened at our wedding
was all my fault.

1315
01:40:09,208 --> 01:40:12,166
I should have got
the official divorce earlier,

1316
01:40:12,250 --> 01:40:14,666
even though we had been separated
for a long time.

1317
01:40:14,750 --> 01:40:17,750
I was wrong to get it done too late.

1318
01:40:18,291 --> 01:40:22,125
But that's not so,
according to what your ex-wife told me.

1319
01:40:24,083 --> 01:40:28,416
She said that,
yes, you did ask for a divorce.

1320
01:40:28,666 --> 01:40:32,666
But she did not want to lose money
to you in a divorce settlement.

1321
01:40:33,000 --> 01:40:35,583
So she refused to agree to a divorce.

1322
01:40:36,250 --> 01:40:37,333
That's not true.

1323
01:40:37,458 --> 01:40:40,791
If she didn't want a divorce,
then how do I have this certificate?

1324
01:40:40,875 --> 01:40:45,041
Because you signed
an agreement with your ex-wife

1325
01:40:45,375 --> 01:40:47,958
that you would not ask
for any of her money

1326
01:40:48,291 --> 01:40:52,291
because you had your hopes set on
taking money from this movie budget.

1327
01:40:52,958 --> 01:40:54,250
What's more,

1328
01:40:54,375 --> 01:40:58,500
this man thinks that this piece of paper
means he can fool me again.

1329
01:40:59,500 --> 01:41:00,875
And did he succeed?

1330
01:41:02,291 --> 01:41:05,916
A guy like this can only fool me once.

1331
01:41:06,000 --> 01:41:08,875
So why did you agree to star in his movie?

1332
01:41:09,250 --> 01:41:10,791
[press members murmuring]

1333
01:41:12,500 --> 01:41:17,166
I'm sure John planned all of this himself.

1334
01:41:17,916 --> 01:41:19,958
The reason I came here today

1335
01:41:20,166 --> 01:41:25,500
is because I wanted everyone
to know the truth about him.

1336
01:41:26,208 --> 01:41:27,625
As for me starring in this movie?

1337
01:41:27,708 --> 01:41:33,625
In this lifetime, I will never work
with this director ever again.

1338
01:41:36,625 --> 01:41:38,125
[press members applauding]

1339
01:41:38,208 --> 01:41:40,791
Thank you, everyone,
for your time and understanding.

1340
01:41:45,333 --> 01:41:46,333
Pang!

1341
01:41:46,416 --> 01:41:47,750
[camera shutters clicking]

1342
01:41:49,541 --> 01:41:52,250
Follow her!
See if Pang will give us an interview!

1343
01:42:07,416 --> 01:42:08,625
[inaudible]

1344
01:42:17,875 --> 01:42:20,583
[producer]
So he just runs like this every day?

1345
01:42:20,750 --> 01:42:21,791
[man] Yes.

1346
01:42:23,583 --> 01:42:24,833
Why is he running?

1347
01:42:25,833 --> 01:42:27,750
He's not making my movie anymore?

1348
01:42:28,083 --> 01:42:30,083
He said he doesn't want to do it anymore.

1349
01:42:30,708 --> 01:42:32,000
Goddammit!

1350
01:42:32,291 --> 01:42:35,541
If he's not going to make a movie,
what the hell is he going to do?

1351
01:42:35,625 --> 01:42:37,416
He said he wants
to be a competitive runner.

1352
01:42:37,500 --> 01:42:38,791
A runner? [chuckles]

1353
01:42:38,875 --> 01:42:39,875
Yeah.

1354
01:42:40,250 --> 01:42:43,666
[producer] This asshole
is some kind of Grump!

1355
01:42:43,791 --> 01:42:44,875
[man] Forrest Gump, sir.

1356
01:42:44,958 --> 01:42:47,625
[producer] Yeah,
he thinks he's Forrest Gump,

1357
01:42:47,958 --> 01:42:49,708
but he's not.

1358
01:42:50,291 --> 01:42:52,333
-He's an artist.
-Hmm.

1359
01:42:52,416 --> 01:42:54,791
He needs to make damn movies.

1360
01:42:54,875 --> 01:42:56,875
[Kheng] We just need to give him
a little bit of time.

1361
01:42:56,958 --> 01:42:58,375
[producer] Screw that!

1362
01:42:58,541 --> 01:43:00,916
I gave him a shitload of time already.

1363
01:43:01,000 --> 01:43:03,666
I should have just listened to my friend.

1364
01:43:04,250 --> 01:43:05,416
What did your friend say?

1365
01:43:05,916 --> 01:43:09,291
He said, "You don't just need money
to make a movie."

1366
01:43:09,416 --> 01:43:10,458
Why is that?

1367
01:43:10,833 --> 01:43:12,208
You also need to be a fool!

1368
01:43:13,208 --> 01:43:15,708
-[laughing]
-[bicycle bell ringing]

1369
01:43:22,291 --> 01:43:24,416
She looks familiar.

1370
01:43:25,625 --> 01:43:27,416
She's the famous actress, Pang.

1371
01:43:27,708 --> 01:43:30,958
Oh. This is Pang.

1372
01:43:31,083 --> 01:43:33,416
That's right.

1373
01:43:34,500 --> 01:43:36,000
[bicycle bell continues ringing]

1374
01:43:40,750 --> 01:43:42,208
Where are you going, Tukkae?

1375
01:43:43,291 --> 01:43:44,666
Nowhere, really.

1376
01:43:45,791 --> 01:43:48,208
Aren't you going to finish your movie?

1377
01:43:50,416 --> 01:43:53,500
What about you? Aren't you going
to get your master's degree abroad?

1378
01:43:54,375 --> 01:43:57,875
Yes, but I want to do
one more movie before I go.

1379
01:43:59,166 --> 01:44:00,208
[Tukkae] What movie?

1380
01:44:01,416 --> 01:44:05,583
It's a movie without a title.

1381
01:44:08,541 --> 01:44:12,958
But I heard that director is
no longer working on it anymore.

1382
01:44:16,500 --> 01:44:21,375
Why not? I saw the first half
of the movie, and it looked promising.

1383
01:44:30,000 --> 01:44:32,000
What about Blood of Suphan Buri?

1384
01:44:34,333 --> 01:44:36,750
I prefer the Chiang Khan story.

1385
01:44:38,916 --> 01:44:41,083
Why do you want to be in this movie?

1386
01:44:44,166 --> 01:44:46,708
Why did you want to make it?

1387
01:44:50,291 --> 01:44:53,375
Because this movie...

1388
01:44:55,083 --> 01:44:56,416
This movie is about you.

1389
01:45:02,875 --> 01:45:05,125
And the reason I want to be in your movie

1390
01:45:09,416 --> 01:45:10,958
is because it is

1391
01:45:13,791 --> 01:45:14,916
about us.

1392
01:45:21,333 --> 01:45:22,833
[kids clapping]

1393
01:45:29,791 --> 01:45:31,208
[men clapping, whistling]

1394
01:45:42,875 --> 01:45:44,625
So he's coming back,
and he wants to make a romance now?

1395
01:45:44,708 --> 01:45:45,708
That's right.

1396
01:45:45,791 --> 01:45:47,708
And what about my Mae Nak Riverside?

1397
01:45:48,166 --> 01:45:49,583
I think that's up to you.

1398
01:45:49,666 --> 01:45:51,250
Up to me? What the hell?

1399
01:45:51,333 --> 01:45:54,375
It's up to that goddamn artist!

1400
01:45:55,083 --> 01:45:56,500
So what do you want to do?

1401
01:45:57,166 --> 01:46:00,916
I get to pick the name for this new movie.

1402
01:46:01,291 --> 01:46:03,666
What are you going to call it?

1403
01:46:04,333 --> 01:46:07,583
Tukkae Loves Pang to Death.
[chuckles]

1404
01:46:07,666 --> 01:46:10,041
-Tukkae Loves Pang to Death?
-That's right.

1405
01:46:10,416 --> 01:46:14,750
I think people will assume
it's a ghost story with that title.

1406
01:46:14,833 --> 01:46:16,583
The hell are you talking about?

1407
01:46:16,916 --> 01:46:18,583
Ghost story?

1408
01:46:18,666 --> 01:46:21,416
Mae Nak, Por Mak, that's a ghost story.

1409
01:46:21,500 --> 01:46:23,458
But if you have "Death" in the title,
people assume a ghost story.

1410
01:46:23,541 --> 01:46:28,125
"To death" is just an expression
that means "a lot." Don't you get it?

1411
01:46:28,208 --> 01:46:29,625
So "to death" means "a lot"?

1412
01:46:29,708 --> 01:46:33,291
-A lot more than "a lot."
-Okay.

1413
01:46:33,375 --> 01:46:34,666
Is "so much" more than "a lot"?

1414
01:46:34,750 --> 01:46:38,041
-"So much" is not enough!
-You're killing me.

1415
01:46:38,125 --> 01:46:39,916
That's closer! Tukkae Loves Pang to Death!

1416
01:46:40,000 --> 01:46:43,375
[Tukkae] Tukkae Loves Pang to Death,
scene 33, take one.

1417
01:46:44,166 --> 01:46:45,541
[music playing]

1418
01:46:49,625 --> 01:46:50,666
Action!

1419
01:47:11,041 --> 01:47:12,291
What did you think, boss?

1420
01:47:19,791 --> 01:47:21,083
That's Nawarat!

1421
01:47:21,166 --> 01:47:22,333
I know. I know.

1422
01:47:58,708 --> 01:48:00,708
[Pang's mother] You like painting,
but what do you want to do 

1423
01:48:00,791 --> 01:48:02,416
when you get older, Tukkae?

1424
01:48:02,500 --> 01:48:05,375
[Tukkae] I want to be a billboard artist
like Master Pong.

1425
01:48:05,708 --> 01:48:08,416
[Pang's mother] What do you want to do 
when you grow up, Pang?

1426
01:48:08,500 --> 01:48:10,000
[Pang] I want to be a movie star!

1427
01:48:10,375 --> 01:48:11,458
[Pang's mother] Really?

1428
01:48:11,541 --> 01:48:13,708
Why do you want to be a movie star, dear?

1429
01:48:13,791 --> 01:48:16,791
[Pang] So I can see myself painted
on a giant billboard someday!

1430
01:48:16,875 --> 01:48:18,000
TUKKAE LOVES PANG TO DEATH

1431
01:48:18,083 --> 01:48:22,250
[Tukkae] If you become a movie star,
I'll paint your billboard myself!

1432
01:48:22,583 --> 01:48:25,041
[Pang] You have to make sure
it's the biggest one ever, okay?

1433
01:48:25,125 --> 01:48:26,333
[Tukkae] Definitely. The biggest one ever!

1434
01:48:26,416 --> 01:48:27,458
[Pang] You promise?

1435
01:48:27,541 --> 01:48:29,291
-[Tukkae] I promise!
-[Pang chuckles]

1436
01:48:31,208 --> 01:48:35,208
PETCH CHIANG KAN

1437
01:48:59,250 --> 01:49:00,333
Grandma,

1438
01:49:00,750 --> 01:49:03,958
why can't we have dinner
at Miss Pang's house?

1439
01:49:05,625 --> 01:49:06,625
[grunting]

1440
01:49:08,291 --> 01:49:09,791
Why would we go there?

1441
01:49:10,250 --> 01:49:11,458
She's right over here!

1442
01:49:13,291 --> 01:49:14,625
-You want a smack?
-[exclaims]

1443
01:49:15,916 --> 01:49:17,750
You two are mean.

1444
01:49:18,500 --> 01:49:22,083
ONE MONTH AFTER OUR MOVIE PREMIERED,

1445
01:49:22,208 --> 01:49:25,916
PANG WENT TO SCHOOL IN CHICAGO

1446
01:49:26,000 --> 01:49:29,875
WHILE I CONTINUED WORK
ON MAE NAK RIVERSCAPE.

1447
01:49:30,000 --> 01:49:35,541
PANG DIDN'T SAY HOW LONG SHE'D BE AWAY.

1448
01:49:35,708 --> 01:49:38,083
SHE ONLY SAID

1449
01:49:38,166 --> 01:49:42,000
THAT SHE'D COME BACK FOR SURE

1450
01:49:42,083 --> 01:49:44,541
BECAUSE SHE KNOWS THAT BACK HOME

1451
01:49:44,666 --> 01:49:49,500
SOMEONE SHE LOVES TO DEATH
IS WAITING FOR HER

1452
01:49:55,000 --> 01:49:56,875
[music playing]

